23/08/2009
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Customs officials at the Captain Andreevo border checkpoint seized more than 97.5kg of high-quality heroin found in a Bulgarian-registered bus travelling from Istanbul, Turkey, to the town of Kurdzhali in southern Bulgaria on Saturday (August 22nd). Police arrested the three bus drivers.
In another case on Saturday, police seized 73kg of heroin at the Lesovo border checkpoint from a minivan with Romanian licence plates travelling from Turkey to Romania. There were no passengers in the minivan and police arrested the driver, a Romanian national. (BGNES, DPA - 22/08/09)
